<paragraph id="8BFD36D586186B3EF9C38AFAF84DF92E" blockId="10.[1563,2007,1678,1717]" box="[1563,2007,1678,1717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">
<heading id="D0B581B986186B3EF9C38AFAF84DF92E" box="[1563,2007,1678,1717]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="73" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686186B3EF9C38AFAF8F4F92E" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1563,1902,1678,1717]" class="Gastropoda" family="Euomphalidae" genus="Straparollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euomphalina" pageId="10" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="brevis" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786186B3EF9C38AFAF8F4F92E" box="[1563,1902,1678,1717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">Straparollus brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC86186B3EF85E8AFAF84DF92E" box="[1926,2007,1678,1717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586186B3EF9A48AAFF8ECF89A" blockId="10.[1660,1910,1755,1793]" box="[1660,1910,1755,1793]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">PI. 3 figs 6-8</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E86186B3FFAE78B24FCA8FCDD" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="10" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586186B3EFAE78B24F871F650" blockId="10.[1294,2276,1872,2507]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">
Description. Shell very small, low-spired trochiform, widely phaneromphous. Protoconch of 5 or 6 smooth whorls with a sharp demarcation between the protoconch and teleoconch. Teleoconch of 
<emphasis id="B936EAC786186B3EF8E28BAEF8F6F79A" box="[1850,1900,2010,2049]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">2Yz</emphasis>
smooth and rounded whorls; whorl profile well arched between sutures; with broadly rounded revolving shoulder on its upper surface and slight flattening above; suture moderately deep; ornamentation of fine growth lines; base and umbilical surface strongly rounded. Aperture almost circular; parietal inductura thin; columellar lip thin, arcuate; outer lip with shallow sinus close to the upper suture, swinging forward below sinus and then rounding backward to cross the lower face and the base with a slight backward obliquity, becoming vertical on the umbilical face.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586186B3EFAE786F8F8CFF494" blockId="10.[1293,2278,2700,3155]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">
<materialsCitation id="3B2A3C8886186B3EFAE786F8F8CFF494" accessionNumber="F78363, F78364, F78365" pageId="10" pageNumber="73" specimenCount="3" typeStatus="holotype">
Types. 
<typeStatus id="54F9887786186B3EFA1386F8F9FDF52F" box="[1483,1639,2700,2740]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">Holotype</typeStatus>
(
<accessionNumber id="9411AB3686186B3EF95486F8F88BF52F" box="[1676,1809,2700,2740]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/F78363" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">F78363</accessionNumber>
) and 2 figured 
<typeStatus id="54F9887786186B3EF79D86F8F77EF52F" box="[2117,2276,2700,2740]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">paratypes</typeStatus>
(
<accessionNumber id="9411AB3686186B3EFAC386CEFA38F57A" box="[1307,1442,2746,2785]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/F78364" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">F78364</accessionNumber>
). There are 20 unfigured 
<typeStatus id="54F9887786186B3EF8A586CEF77EF57A" box="[1917,2276,2746,2785]" isOtherTypeStatus="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">additional specimens</typeStatus>
(
<accessionNumber id="9411AB3686186B3EFAC2869DFA04F494" box="[1306,1438,2793,2831]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/F78365" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">F78365</accessionNumber>
) from the type locality.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586186B3EFAE78763F8A1F4F7" blockId="10.[1293,2278,2700,3155]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">
Type locality. Behind 'Kyndalyn' homestead, 
<quantity id="4CBA9B3086186B3EF7A38763F77FF4A5" box="[2171,2277,2839,2878]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="73" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
south-west of Somerton, NSW.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586186B3EFAE68707FA5CF46D" blockId="10.[1293,2278,2700,3155]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">Stratigraphic position. From base of oolitic limestone, in the Kyndalyn Mudstone Member of the Merlewood Formation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586186B3EFAE78789F7F0F3BE" blockId="10.[1293,2278,2700,3155]" box="[1343,2154,3069,3109]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">
Geographic distribution. 
<typeStatus id="54F9887786186B3EF8C28789F8EAF3BE" box="[1818,1904,3069,3109]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">Type</typeStatus>
locality only.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586186B3EFAE68058F791F3C8" blockId="10.[1293,2278,2700,3155]" box="[1342,2059,3116,3155]" pageId="10" pageNumber="73">Geological age. Middle or late Visean.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586196B3FFEC48DF4FB24FE4D" blockId="11.[234,1217,384,838]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">
Etymology. Derived from the Latin word 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686196B3FFB838DF4FB5AFE33" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1115,1216,384,424]" class="Gastropoda" family="Euomphalidae" genus="Straparollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euomphalina" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786196B3FFB838DF4FB5AFE33" box="[1115,1216,384,424]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning short; referring to the low spire of the shell.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586196B3FFEC38DA9FCA8FCDD" blockId="11.[234,1217,384,838]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">
Remarks. This is smaller in size than any other species referred to subgenus 
<emphasis id="B936EAC786196B3FFD208E7FFC4BFDA8" box="[760,977,523,563]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686196B3FFD208E7FFC56FDA8" authorityName="de Montfort" authorityYear="1810" box="[760,972,523,563]" class="Gastropoda" family="Euomphalidae" genus="Straparollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euomphalina" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Straparollus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This species has a larger pleural angle (145-150°) than in S. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686196B3FFB808E4EFD81FD14" authority="Dun &amp; Benson" authorityName="Dun &amp; Benson" authorityYear="1920" class="Gastropoda" family="Euomphalidae" genus="Straparollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euomphalina" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786196B3FFB808E4EFB5AFDFA" box="[1112,1216,570,609]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">davidi</emphasis>
Dun &amp; Benson
</taxonomicName>
(120-130°) and the 
<typeStatus id="54F9887786196B3FFC0E8E1CFBBAFD14" box="[982,1056,616,655]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686196B3FFF328EE1FD60FD26" authority="Montfort" authorityName="Montfort" box="[234,762,661,701]" class="Gastropoda" family="Euomphalidae" genus="Straparollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euomphalina" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dionysii">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786196B3FFF328EE1FDC8FD26" box="[234,594,661,701]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Straparollus dionysii</emphasis>
Montfort
</taxonomicName>
(pleural angle about 80°) from 
<collectingCountry id="F355764586196B3FFE8D8EB0FE7DFD70" box="[341,487,708,747]" name="Belgium" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Belgium</collectingCountry>
. Another European species 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686196B3FFC378EB0FDA1FC82" authority="(Leveille)" baseAuthorityName="Leveille" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Gastropoda" family="Euomphalidae" genus="Straparollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euomphalina" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="levigatus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786196B3FFC378EB0FE18FC82" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Straparollus levigatus</emphasis>
(Leveille)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686196B3FFD7A8E85FEE6FCDD" authority="de Koninck" authorityName="de Koninck" class="Gastropoda" family="Euomphalidae" genus="Straparollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euomphalina" pageId="11" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="planorbiformis">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786196B3FFD7A8E85FB1EFC82" box="[674,1156,753,793]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Straparollus planorbiformis</emphasis>
de Koninck
</taxonomicName>
are rather flatly coiled.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
